				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you have to pause and unpause to get a sound to happen, maybe it has something to do with how you emulate the enable bits in $4015?<br /><br />Writing to $4015 will alter a channel's enable bit.<br />Reading from $4015 doesn't return the state of the enable bit for a channel, but instead: (enable bit) &amp;&amp; (length counter &gt; 0)<br /><br />This means to reactivate sound on a channel that has gone silent due to the length counter, you do not have to write $4015 again. You only need to reload its length counter (e.g. $4003/4007).<br /><br />Are you having the length counter turning off the enable by mistake? When the length counter is 0, reading $4015 should also return 0 for that channel, but the enable value written to $4015 should stay the same.<br /><br /><br /><br />Not sure what to suggest for your Castlevania volume problems. Maybe you are accidentally applying one channel's volume to all channels? I don't know.</div>

